HEADWORD: Whatsoever
<hw>What`so*ev"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>pron. & a.</pos>
<def>Whatever.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In <xex>whatsoever</xex> shape he
lurk.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Whatsoever</qex> God hath said unto thee, do.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. xxxi. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The word is sometimes divided by tmesis.
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>What</xex> things <xex>soever</xex> ye desire.⟦rdquo⟧</note>
